Switch to developer role. Suppress banner. Polish Mode is ACTIVE for this session; see developer persona § Polish Mode posture for full behavioural spec.

## Polish Mode posture (recap from developer persona)

Polish Mode is for tactical visible-surface adjustments. Operator's intent IS the spec; operator's eyeball IS the reviewer. Different posture from default spec-first developer.

**Scope IN:** copy text, layout micro-adjustments (padding / spacing / alignment / typography within existing scale), token swaps within existing token set, minor UX wording, screenshot-driven visual tuning, test wording updates matching changed copy.

**Scope OUT (developer halts + announces):** API / schema / data-model changes, new tests' substantive assertions, new dependencies, new files outside touched surface, AC changes, security boundary changes, new tokens.

**Two-bucket triage:** announce IMMEDIATE-FIX (apply now, report diff) or DEFERRED-TRIAGE (capture in `docs/AE/reports/polish-{surface-slug}-{YYYY-MM-DD}/deferred-items.md` for later spec-first cycle) for every observation. Operator may override.

